This paper discusses the measurement of Internet censorship, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the challenges of data collection and analysis, which involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-offs of decisions made by each platform, which involves system and information theory (cs.SI) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
